http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Madurai/12-arrested-for-defying-jallikattu-ban/article14006691.ece

The police, on Monday, arrested 12 villagers of Vadavalam near Karambakudi on a charge of instigating violence during an attempt to conduct “jallikattu” at the village on Sunday.A cross-section of people threw stones and untying one of the bulls at the village, defying the ban.When police resorted to lathicharge, the people, in their retaliation, damaged the windscreens of a police vehicle.M. Kalaivani, a police constable, and G. Suresh, a Home Guard, were injured following throwing of stones. The Sembattu Viduthi police, on Monday, registered a case against 12 persons and arrested them.